speakers.bio: Alex has been doing professional client-side development over the last decade in a variety of UI toolkits and libraries that spanned Motif, MFC, VB, Ada, Delphi, Swing and SWT. Since 2009 he's been part of the Android team at Google. He has a particular interest in creating polished, responsive and well-behaving, user-facing applications that help the end users achieve their goals quickly and painlessly.
speakers.name: Alex Korovyansky

speakers.bio: Kirill is a software engineer at Google, working on the platform powering the Google Art Project. Prior to joining Google in 2011, he worked at Aldebaran Robotics doing computer vision.
speakers.name: Kirill Boyarshinov

speakers.bio: Yulia is a designer focused on speed of innovation and team-work that create simple, beautiful solutions for a global audience. She works as a Staff Designer and Design Evangelist at Google X, a new product lab at Google. To date, Nadya has run 60 design sprints at Google, including projects for Google [X], Chrome and Ads & Commerce.
speakers.name: Yulia Naychuk

speakers.bio: Alexey was the technical lead for Google Santa Tracker, a delightful project built by a group of merry volunteers. When not tracking Saint Nick, he is a senior engineer on the Google Developer Relations team, focusing primarily on the Google Maps APIs (mobile and web). You'll often find Chris cruising around on a longboard near Google's offices in Pyrmont, Sydney.
speakers.name: Alexey Zinoviev

speakers.bio: Ekaterina has been with Google since 2012, where she currently works as a Sr. Designer on Google Maps. She brings projects from development through to completion, defines user interface for new and existing products and features, develops high level mockups, motion graphics and prototypes, to effectively communicate interaction and visual design ideas. She has experience integrating design across multiple platforms, from desktop, mobile, TV, and gaming consoles.
speakers.name: Ekaterina Pender

sessions.description: DevFest's much-anticipated kickoff event will make you among the first developers to see what we've been working on here at Google. If you're not joining us at Moscone, grab some popcorn, kick back and enjoy the show directly from your Android powered device.
sessions.title: Keynote

sessions.description: Build the best version of your app. Come learn tips and tricks for building truly great Android apps - get the most out of Android Studio’s design tools, master the intricacies of Gradle, tune your client performance with procstats and systrace, simplify your backend with Google Play services, and more. Android experts will be on hand to tear down your app … and then rebuild it. We have the technology.
sessions.title: Android in Cube
